description.narrative: UNICEF continued to be a partner of choice around maternal and child nutrition to the Government of Indonesia during the COVID-19 pandemic. With the Ministry of Health, UNICEF developed, disseminated and socialized the National Technical Guidance on the continuity of eight essential nutrition services in the context of COVID-19 pandemic, with capacity building workshops to accelerate implementation. UNICEF also supported the government in developing and disseminating a wide range of social behavior change communication materials and tools on essential nutrition services, which have reached more than 6 million people nationwide. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:15/07/2020
